    <h2 id=3D"idx_how_to_convert_hectares_to_acres">How to Convert Hectares=
 to Acres</h2>

<p>
    The fastest way to convert hectares to acres is to use this simple form=
ula:
</p>
<p>
    <span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">acres =3D hectares =C3=97 2.47=
1054</span>
</p>
<p>
    The area in acres is equal to the area in hectares multiplied by 2.4710=
54.
    Since one acre is equal to 2.471054 hectares<sup class=3D"reference_num=
ber reference_link"><a href=3D"https://nauticalcharts.noaa.gov/publications=
/coast-pilot/files/cp6/CPB6_C01_WEB.pdf" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener"=
>[1]</a></sup>, that's the conversion ratio used in the formula.
</p>
<div class=3D"panel panel--bg-grey">
    <p>
        <strong>For example,</strong> here's how to convert 5 hectares to a=
cres using the formula above.
    </p>
    <p>
        <span class=3D"formula formula--bg-primary">acres =3D (5 ha =C3=97 =
2.471054) =3D 12.355269 ac</span>
    </p>
</div>
    <div class=3D"row">
        <div class=3D"article-thumbnail col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1">
            <img src=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/a/img/unit-conversio=
n/acre-to-hectare-conversion-scale.png" alt=3D"conversion scale showing hec=
tares and equivalent acres area values" width=3D"3000" height=3D"850" loadi=
ng=3D"lazy">
        </div>
    </div>
    <h3 id=3D"idx_how_many_acres_are_in_a_hectare">How Many Acres Are in a =
Hectare?</h3>
    <p>
        There are <strong>2.471054</strong> acres in a hectare, which is wh=
y we use this value in the formula above.
    </p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_1_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthriv=
e-content adthrive-content-1" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>
    <p>
        <span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">1 ha =3D 2.471054 ac</span=
>
    </p>

<p>
    Hectares and acres are both units used to measure <a href=3D"https://ww=
w.inchcalculator.com/convert/area/">area</a>. Keep reading to learn more ab=
out each unit of measure.
</p>

        <div>
        <h2 id=3D"idx_what_is_a_hectare">What Is a Hectare?</h2>
        <p>
    One hectare is equal to 10,000 <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.co=
m/convert/from-square-meter/">square meters</a>,<sup class=3D"reference_num=
ber reference_link"><a href=3D"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/us/dictiona=
ry/english/hectare" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">[2]</a></sup> or the=
 area of a square with 100 <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/conver=
t/from-meter/">meter</a> sides.
</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_2_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-co=
ntent adthrive-content-2" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>
        <p>
                                        The  hectare is an <a href=3D"https=
://www.inchcalculator.com/si-international-system-of-units/">SI</a> accepte=
d unit for area for use with the metric system.                In the metri=
c system, "hecto" is the prefix for 10<sup>2</sup>.                        =
        Hectares can be abbreviated as <em>ha</em>; for example, 1 hectare =
can be written as 1 ha.                                    </p>
                <p>
            Learn more about <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/conv=
ert/from-hectare/">hectares</a>.
        </p>
    </div>
        <div>
        <h2 id=3D"idx_what_is_an_acre">What Is an Acre?</h2>
        <p>
    One acre is defined as the area equal to a space that is one chain (66 =
ft) by one furlong (660 ft), or 10 square chains.<sup class=3D"reference_nu=
mber reference_link"><a href=3D"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/hb/2019/N=
IST.HB.44-2019.pdf" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">[3]</a></sup>    Tha=
t's equal to 43,560 <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/convert/from-=
square-foot/">square feet</a> or 1/640 of a <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalc=
ulator.com/convert/from-square-mile/">square mile</a> for those unfamiliar =
with those units of measure.
</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_3_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-co=
ntent adthrive-content-3" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>
<div class=3D"article-thumbnail article-thumbnail-width-50">
    <img decoding=3D"async" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://www.inchcalcula=
tor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/acre-dimensions.png" alt=3D"illustration=
 showing the size of an acre is a parcel of land that is 66 feet by 660 fee=
t." width=3D"1000" height=3D"1613" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-28=
53">
</div>
        <p>
                                        The  acre is a US customary and imp=
erial unit of area.                                                Acres ca=
n be abbreviated as <em>ac</em>; for example, 1 acre can be written as 1 ac=
.                                    </p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_4_tabl=
et" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-content adthrive-content-4" style=3D"min=
-height: 250px;"></div>
        <p>
    You can use an <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/acreage-calcul=
ator/">acreage calculator</a> to measure the area of a plot of land in acre=
s by locating the boundaries on a map.
</p>
        <p>
            Learn more about <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/conv=
ert/from-acre/">acres</a>.
        </p>
